Lagos State Government on Sunday confirmed the death of three coronavirus patients. The state health commissioner Akin Abayomi in a tweet said the number of death from coronavirus has risen to 28. “3 more #COVID19 related deaths were recorded, bringing total of such deaths in Lagos to 28,” Abayomi said. Lagos State on Saturday said it discharged 22 coronavirus patients who recovered from the disease. The discharged patients- eight females and 14 males, Abayomi said are all Nigerians. “This Brings the total number of #COVID19 discharged patients in Lagos to 247,” Abayomi said. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) late Saturday confirmed 62 new cases of coronavirus in Lagos State, bringing the total number of cases to 1,084.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .